PEP is an inbred line that carries gene B (BB). It is iso- genic to "Early Prolific Straightneck" (B+B+). Reference: Shifriss, O. 1981. (The foregoing capital "B's" have an underscore and the "+'s" are superscripts.)

Bush habit, fruits orange. Yellow pigmentation occurs prior to anthesis. As fruit grow it becomes progressively more deeply orange externally and internally. Immature fruits not over 2 inches in diameter can be steamed and eaten whole. Baked mature fruits have superior flavor, tenderness, and freedom from fiber.

Butter yellow semi-crookneck. Typically picked at 6 inch length. Compact bush plant has open structure, making for easy picking. Notably smaller bush than other semi-crooknecks. Large leaves provide fruit with excellent protection from sunburn.

Winter type. Cotyledon 52 mm long and 30 mm wide, apex rounded, obscure veining, medium green. Plant composed of long vines, prickly. Main stem round, 19 mm in diameter at midpoint of first internode, 335 cm ave. length, ave. number of internodes 42. Leaves reniform shaped, deep lobed, margin dentate and frilled, 25 cm wide and 24 cm long at third internode, ave. of 25 per plant, smooth surface, dorsal surface soft hairy, ventral surface bristled, dark green, not blotched, 26 cm petiole length. Pistillate 20 cm in diameter, ovary drum-like, pedicel 2 cm long, margin curved and frilled, sepals 2 mm wide and 11 mm long, orange. Staminate sepals 21 mm long and 3 mm wide, pedicel 19 cm long, orange. Fruit 13 cm long, 14 cm wide at stem end, and 14 cm wide at blossom end, 1270 grams ave. weight, Connecticut field shape, depressed apex, depressed base, inconspicuous ribs, shallow and narrow rib furrows, surface smooth, no warts, depressed blossom scar button. Rind 2 mm thick at medial, soft, regular color pattern, grayish-buff color, pink self or ground, pink stripes, pink lace, no specific location of pattern colors. Flesh 15 mm thick at blossom end, 15 mm thick at medial, and 17 mm thick at stem end, granular, firm, moist, slightly sweet, excellent quality, pink. Seed cavity 8 cm long and 10 cm wide, conforms to fruit shape, placental tissue sparse, center core prominent. Fruit stalks 7 cm long and 2 cm in diameter, irregular, not twisted, tapered, slightly curved, hard, deep farrows, spiny, expanded attachment end, detaches with difficulty, medium green, expanded portion medium yellow. Seeds 15 mm long, 8 mm wide, and 3 mm thick, smooth, buff, dull, curved and wedge-like margin, moderately easy to separate from pulp, 9 grams/100 seeds, 490 seeds per fruit, normal. Not tested for disease or insect resistance. Most likely resembles Spookie for plant habit, leaf type, flower type, and fruit shape, Jersey Golden Acorn for fruit color, and Small Sugar Pie for culinary type.

Summer (vegetable marrow) type pumpkin.  Cotyledon: 46 mm long, 28 mm wide, rounded apex, plainly visible veining, medium green color.  Plant: semi-bush and prickly.  Main stem: angled, 52 mm diameter at midpoint of first internode, 105 cm average length, 22 internodes on average.  Leaves: broad triangular, deep lobed, dentate and frilled margin, 38 cm wide, 30 cm long, smooth surface, dorsal and ventral surfaces bristled, medium green color, not blotched, 48 cm petiole length.  Flower (pistillate): 22 cm diameter, drum-like ovary, 5 cm pedicel length, curved and plain margin, 1.5 mm sepal width, 10 mm sepel length, orange color.  Flower (staminate): 22 mm sepal length, 2.5 mm sepal width, 24 cm pedicel length, orange color.  Fruit: 29 cm length, 24 cm width (stem end), 26 cm width (blossom end), 4985 gram average weight, Connecticut Field shape, rounded apex, depressed base, prominant ribs, medium deep and narrow rib furrows, smooth fruit surface, no warts, depressed blossom scar button.  Rind: 3 mm thick at medial, hard, irregular color pattern, yellow-orange color, orange color in a lace pattern in a non-specific location.  Flesh: 32 mm thick at blossom end, 34 mm thick at medial end, 25 mm thick at stem end, stringy, firm, and moist texture, slightly sweet flavor, good quality, yellow-orange color.  Seed cavity: 24 cm length, 19 cm width, conforms to fruit shape, moderately abundant placental tissue, inconspicuous center core.  Fruit stalks 90 cm length, 3.4 cm diameter, irregular, not twisted, tapered, straight, hard texture, deep farrows, spiny surface, slightly expanded attachment end, detaches with difficulty, dark green color.  Seeds: 17 mm length, 9.5 mm width, 3 mm thick, wrinkled face surface, gray-green color, dull luster, curved and wedge-like margin, moderately easy separation from pulp, 14 grams per 100 seeds, 318 seeds per fruit, naked.  Susceptible to powdery mildew and squash bug.  Most closely resembles Cinderella for plant habit, leaf type, flower type, and fruit shape, Big Tom for fruit color, and Small Sugar for culinary type.

Winter type squash.  Cotyledon: 43 mm long and 28 mm wide (measured at appearance of second leaf bud), rounded apex, plainly visible veining, medium green with light green veining.  Plant: semi-bush and prickly.  Main stem: round, ridged, 15 mm diameter at midpoint of first internode, 260 cm average length, 34 internodes on average.  Leaves: ovate and deep lobed shape, denticulate and flat margin, 38 cm wide, 27 cm long, smooth surface, dorsal surface soft hairy, ventral surface soft hairy, medium green, blotched with gray, 27 cm petiole length.  Flower (pistillate): 5 cm diameter, turbinate ovary, 2 cm pedicel length, straight and plain margin, 1 mm sepal width and 20 mm sepal width (measured at midpoint), deep yellow color.  Flower (staminate): 20 mm sepal length and 1 mm sepal width (measured at midpoint), 12 cm pedicel length, deep yellow color.  Fruit (market maturity): 14 cm length, 9 cm width at stem end, 10 cm width at medial, 6 cm width at blossom end, 680 gram average weight, acorn shape, taper pointed apex, flattened base, prominant ribs, medium deep and wide rib furrows, fruit surface smooth, no warts, slightly extended blossom scar button.  Rind: 1 mm thick at medial, hard, regular color pattern, white.  Flesh: 27 mm thick at blossom end, 21 mm thick at medial, 23 mm thick at stem end, fine or stringy, firm, and moist texture, slightly sweet flavor, excellent quality, creamy yellow color.  Seed cavity (sectioned apex to base): 9 cm length, 6 cm width, conforms to fruit shape, sparse placental tissue, inconspicuous center core.  Fruit stalks: 5 cm length, 1 cm diameter, irregular, ridged, not twisted, tapered, slightly curved, hard texture, shallow farrows, rough surface, slightly expanded attachment end, detaches easily, medium green color (darker green at point of attachment).  Seeds: 13 mm length, 8 mm width, 2 mm thick, smooth face surface, buff color, dull luster, straight and wedge-like margin, easy separation from pulp, 10 grams per 100 seeds, 156 seeds per fruit, normal.  Most closely resembles Table Queen for plant habit, leaf type, flower type, fruit shape, and culinary type, and White Patty Pan for fruit color (at maturity).
